From (H7495) rapha' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has cured; Rephajah, the name of five Israelites -- Rephaiah. see HEBREW (H7495) rapha' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H7503) raphah; slackness -- feebleness. see HEBREW (H7503) raphah
A primitive root; to trample, i.e. Prostrate -- humble self, submit self.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7511) raphac -- stamp. see HEBREW (H7511) raphac
From (H7511) raphac; a raft (as flat on the water) -- flote. see HEBREW (H7511) raphac
A primitive root; to recline -- lean.
A primitive root; to trample, i.e. Roil water -- foul, trouble.
From (H7515) raphas; mud (as roiled) -- mire. see HEBREW (H7515) raphas
Probably from (H7503) raphah; a stall for cattle (from their resting there) -- stall. see HEBREW (H7503) raphah
Contracted from (H7533) ratsats; a fragment -- piece. see HEBREW (H7533) ratsats
A primitive root; to run; also to delight in -- accept, run.
A primitive root; probably to look askant, i.e. (figuratively) be jealous -- leap.

column7: to be pleased with, accept favorably
column8: be acceptable, accomplish, set affection, approve, consent with
column9: A primitive root; to be pleased with; specifically, to satisfy a debt -- (be) accept(-able), accomplish, set affection, approve, consent with, delight (self), enjoy, (be, have a) favour(-able), like, observe, pardon, (be, have, take) please(-ure), reconcile self.

column8: be acceptable, delight, desire, favor, good pleasure, own, self, voluntary will, as
column9: Or ratson {raw-tsone'}; from (H7521) ratsah; delight (especially as shown) -- (be) acceptable(-ance, -ed), delight, desire, favour, (good) pleasure, (own, self, voluntary) will, as...(what) would. see HEBREW (H7521) ratsah

column8: put to death, kill, manslayer, murderer
column9: A primitive root; properly, to dash in pieces, i.e. Kill (a human being), especially to murder -- put to death, kill, (man-)slay(-er), murder(-er).
From (H7523) ratsach; a crushing; specifically, a murder-cry -- slaughter, sword. see HEBREW (H7523) ratsach
From (H7521) ratsah; delight; Ritsjah, an Israelite -- Rezia. see HEBREW (H7521) ratsah

column7: a king of Aram (Syria), also an Israelite
column9: Probably for (H7522) ratsown; Retsin, the name of a Syrian and of an Israelite -- Rezin. see HEBREW (H7522) ratsown
A primitive root; to pierce -- bore.
A denominative from (H7529) retseph; to tessellate, i.e. Embroider (as if with bright stones) -- pave. see HEBREW (H7529) retseph
For (H7565) resheph; a red-hot stone (for baking) -- coal. see HEBREW (H7565) resheph
The same as (H7529) retseph; Retseph, a place in Assyrian -- Rezeph. see HEBREW (H7529) retseph
Feminine of (H7529) retseph; a hot stone; also a tessellated pavement -- live coal, pavement. see HEBREW (H7529) retseph
The same as (H7531) ritspah; Ritspah, an Israelitess -- Rizpah. see HEBREW (H7531) ritspah

column8: break, bruise, crush, discourage, oppress, struggle together
column9: A primitive root; to crack in pieces, literally or figuratively -- break, bruise, crush, discourage, oppress, struggle together.
From (H7556) raqaq in its original sense; emaciated (as if flattened out) -- lean((-fleshed)), thin. see HEBREW (H7556) raqaq

column7: but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless
column8: but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless
column9: The same as (H7534) raq as a noun; properly, leanness, i.e. (figuratively) limitation; only adverbial, merely, or conjunctional, although -- but, even, except, howbeit howsoever, at the least, nevertheless, nothing but, notwithstanding, only, save, so (that), surely, yet (so), in any wise. see HEBREW (H7534) raq
From (H7556) raqaq; spittle -- spit(-ting, -tle). see HEBREW (H7556) raqaq
A primitive root; to decay (as by worm-eating) -- rot.
From (H7537) raqab; decay (by caries) -- rottenness (thing). see HEBREW (H7537) raqab
From (H7538) raqab; decay (by caries) -- rotten. see HEBREW (H7538) raqab
A primitive root; properly, to stamp, i.e. To spring about (wildly or for joy) -- dance, jump, leap, skip.
Feminine of (H7534) raq; properly, thinness, i.e. The side of the head -- temple. see HEBREW (H7534) raq

column7: a city in Dan near Joppa
column9: From (H7534) raq; thinness; Rakkon, a place in Palestine -- Rakkon. see HEBREW (H7534) raq

column7: to mix or compound oil or ointment
column8: apothecary, compound, make ointment, prepare, spice
column9: A primitive root; to perfume -- apothecary, compound, make (ointment), prepare, spice.
From (H7543) raqach; properly, perfumery, i.e. (by implication) spicery (for flavor) -- spiced. see HEBREW (H7543) raqach
From (H7542) Raqqown; an aromatic -- confection, ointment. see HEBREW (H7542) Raqqown
From (H7543) raqach; a male perfumer -- apothecary. see HEBREW (H7543) raqach
From (H7543) raqach; a scented substance -- perfume. see HEBREW (H7543) raqach
Feminine of (H7547) raqquach; a female perfumer -- confectioner. see HEBREW (H7547) raqquach
From (H7554) raqa'; properly, an expanse, i.e. The firmament or (apparently) visible arch of the sky -- firmament. see HEBREW (H7554) raqa'
From, (H7556) raqaq in its original sense; a thin cake; -- cake, wafer. see HEBREW (H7556) raqaq
A primitive root; to variegate color, i.e. Embroider; by implication, to fabricate -- embroiderer, needlework, curiously work.

column7: having many colors, a Midianite king, also two Israelites, also a city in Benjamin
column9: From (H7551) raqam; versi-color; Rekem, the name of a place in Palestine, also of a Midianite and an Israelite -- Rekem. see HEBREW (H7551) raqam

column8: broidered work, divers colors, raiment of needlework on both sides
column9: From (H7551) raqam; variegation of color; specifically, embroidery -- broidered (work), divers colours, (raiment of) needlework (on both sides). see HEBREW (H7551) raqam

column7: to beat, stamp, beat out, spread out
column8: beat, make broad, spread abroad forth, over, out, into plates, stamp, stretch
column9: A primitive root; to pound the earth (as a sign of passion); by analogy to expand (by hammering); by implication, to overlay (with thin sheets of metal) -- beat, make broad, spread abroad (forth, over, out, into plates), stamp, stretch.
From (H7554) raqa'; beaten out, i.e. A (metallic) plate -- broad. see HEBREW (H7554) raqa'
A primitive root; to spit -- spit.
From (H7556) raqaq in its original sense of diffusing; a beach (as expanded shingle); Rakkath, a place in Palestine -- Rakkath. see HEBREW (H7556) raqaq
From an unused root meaning to have leave; a permit -- grant.
A primitive root; to record -- note.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7559) rasham -- sign, write. see HEBREW (H7559) rasham

column8: condemn, make trouble, vex, be commit, deal, depart, do wickedly,
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, do or declare) wrong; by implication, to disturb, violate -- condemn, make trouble, vex, be (commit, deal, depart, do) wicked(-ly, -ness).
From (H7561) rasha'; a wrong (especially moral) -- iniquity, wicked(-ness). see HEBREW (H7561) rasha'

column8: condemned, guilty, ungodly, wicked man, that did wrong
column9: From (H7561) rasha'; morally wrong; concretely, an (actively) bad person -- + condemned, guilty, ungodly, wicked (man), that did wrong. see HEBREW (H7561) rasha'
Feminine of (H7562) resha'; wrong (especially moral) -- fault, wickedly(-ness). see HEBREW (H7562) resha'

column8: arrow, burning coal, burning heat, spark, hot thunderbolt
column9: From (H8313) saraph; a live coal; by analogy lightning; figuratively, an arrow, (as flashing through the air); specifically, fever -- arrow, (burning) coal, burning heat, + spark, hot thunderbolt. see HEBREW (H8313) saraph
The same as (H7565) resheph; Resheph, an Israelite -- Resheph. see HEBREW (H7565) resheph
A primitive root; to demolish -- impoverish.
From (H3423) yarash; a net (as catching animals) -- net(- work). see HEBREW (H3423) yarash
From (H7576) rathaq; a chain -- chain. see HEBREW (H7576) rathaq
A primitive root; to boil -- boil.
From (H7570) rathach; a boiling -- X (boil) well. see HEBREW (H7570) rathach
From (H7576) rathaq; a chain -- chain. see HEBREW (H7576) rathaq
A primitive root; to yoke up (to the pole of a vehicle) -- bind.
Or rothem {ro'-them}; from (H7573) ratham; the Spanish broom (from its pole-like stems) -- juniper (tree). see HEBREW (H7573) ratham
Feminine of (H7574) rethem; Rithmah, a place in the Desert -- Rithmah. see HEBREW (H7574) rethem
A primitive root; to fasten -- bind.
Feminine passive participle of (H7576) rathaq; something fastened, i.e. A chain -- chain. see HEBREW (H7576) rathaq
For (H7374) retet; terror -- trembling. see HEBREW (H7374) retet
A primitive root; to bale up water -- (woman to) draw(-er, water).
A primitive root; to rumble or moan -- X mightily, roar.
From (H7580) sha'ag; a rumbling or moan -- roaring. see HEBREW (H7580) sha'ag

column7: to make a din or crash, crash into ruins
column8: be desolate, make a rushing, lay waste
column9: A primitive root; to rush; by implication, to desolate -- be desolate, (make a) rush(-ing), (lay) waste.
A primitive root (identical with (H7582) sha'ah through the idea of whirling to giddiness); to stun, i.e. (intransitively) be astonished -- wonder. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah
From (H7582) sha'ah; a tempest (as rushing) -- desolation. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah

column7: underworld (place to which people descend at death)
column9: Or shol {sheh-ole'}; from (H7592) sha'al; Hades or the world of the dead (as if a subterranean retreat), including its accessories and inmates -- grave, hell, pit. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al

column7: asked (of Yah), first king of Isr., also an Edomite and two Israelites
column9: Passive participle of (H7592) sha'al; asked; Shaul, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites -- Saul, Shaul. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al
Patronymic from (H7856) Sitnan; a Shaulite or descendant of Shaul -- Shaulites. see HEBREW (H7856) Sitnan

column7: a roar (of waters, etc.), din, crash, uproar
column9: From (H7582) sha'ah; uproar (as of rushing); by implication, destruction -- X horrible, noise, pomp, rushing, tumult (X -uous). see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah
From an unused root meaning to push aside; contempt -- despite(-ful).
For active part of (H7750) suwt (compare (H7589) sh'at); one contemning -- that (which) despise(-d). see HEBREW (H7750) suwt see HEBREW (H7589) sh'at
From (H7582) sha'ah; desolation -- destruction. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah

column8: ask counsel, on, beg, borrow, lay to charge, consult, demand, desire,
column9: Or shael {shaw-ale'}; a primitive root; to inquire; by implication, to request; by extension, to demand -- ask (counsel, on), beg, borrow, lay to charge, consult, demand, desire, X earnestly, enquire, + greet, obtain leave, lend, pray, request, require, + salute, X straitly, X surely, wish.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7592) sha'al -- ask, demand, require. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al

column7: an Israelite with a foreign wife
column9: From (H7592) sha'al; request; Sheal, an Israelite -- Sheal. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al
(Aramaic) from (H7593) sh'el; properly, a question (at law), i.e. Judicial decision or mandate -- demand. see HEBREW (H7593) sh'el
Or shelah (1 Samuel 1:17) {shay-law'}; from (H7592) sha'al; a petition; by implication, a loan -- loan, petition, request. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al

column7: I have asked of God, an Israelite name
column9: Or Shaltiy(el {shal-tee-ale'}; from (H7592) sha'al and (H410) 'el; I have asked God; Shealtiel, an Israelite -- Shalthiel, Shealtiel. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: I have asked of God, an Israelite name
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7597) Sh'altiy'el -- Shealtiel. see HEBREW (H7597) Sh'altiy'el

column7: to be at ease or at peace, rest securely
column8: be at ease, be quiet, rest
column9: A primitive root; to loll, i.e. Be peaceful -- be at ease, be quiet, rest. See also (H1052) Beyth Sh'an. see HEBREW (H1052) Beyth Sh'an
From (H7599) sha'an; secure; in a bad sense, haughty -- that is at ease, quiet, tumult. Compare (H7946) shal'anan. see HEBREW (H7599) sha'an see HEBREW (H7946) shal'anan
A primitive root; to plunder -- spoil.

column7: to gasp, pant, pant after, long for
column8: desire earnestly, devour, haste, pant, snuff up, swallow up
column9: A primitive root; to inhale eagerly; figuratively, to cover; by implication, to be angry; also to hasten -- desire (earnestly), devour, haste, pant, snuff up, swallow up.
From (H7604) sha'ar; barm or yeast-cake (as swelling by fermentation) -- leaven. see HEBREW (H7604) sha'ar

column8: leave, be left, let, remain, remnant, reserve, the rest
column9: A primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. Be (causatively, make) redundant -- leave, (be) left, let, remain, remnant, reserve, the rest.
From (H7604) sha'ar; a remainder -- X other, remnant, residue, rest. see HEBREW (H7604) sha'ar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7605) sh'ar -- X whatsoever more, residue, rest. see HEBREW (H7605) sh'ar

column8: body, flesh, food, near kinsman near nigh of kin
column9: From (H7604) sha'ar; flesh (as swelling out), as living or for food; generally food of any kind; figuratively, kindred by blood -- body, flesh, food, (near) kin(-sman, -swoman), near (nigh) (of kin). see HEBREW (H7604) sha'ar
Feminine of (H7607) sh'er; female kindred by blood -- near kinswomen. see HEBREW (H7607) sh'er
The same as (H7608) sha'arah; Sheerah, an Israelitess -- Sherah. see HEBREW (H7608) sha'arah

column7: a remnant shall return, son of Isaiah
column9: From (H7605) sh'ar and (H7725) shuwb; a remnant will return; Shear-Jashub, the symbolic name of one of Isaiah's sons -- Shear-jashub. see HEBREW (H7605) sh'ar see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From (H7604) sha'ar; a remainder or residual (surviving, final) portion -- that had escaped, be left, posterity, remain(-der), remnant, residue, rest. see HEBREW (H7604) sha'ar
From (H7582) sha'ah; devastation -- desolation. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah

column8: be accepted, dignity, highness, raise up self, rising
column9: From (H5375) nasa'; an elevation or leprous scab; figuratively, elation or cheerfulness; exaltation in rank or character -- be accepted, dignity, excellency, highness, raise up self, rising. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'

column4: proper name, of a people and territory
column7: a territory in S.W. Arabia, also the name of one or more descendant of Noah
column9: Of foreign origin; Sheba, the name of three early progenitors of tribes and of an Ethiopian district -- Sheba, Sabeans.
Patronymic from (H7614) Shba'; a Shebaite or descendant of Sheba -- Sabean. see HEBREW (H7614) Shba'
From an unused root meaning to break up; a fragment, i.e. Ruin -- broken in pieces.

column8: bring away, carry, carry away, lead, lead away, take captives, take away
column9: A primitive root; to transport into captivity -- (bring away, carry, carry away, lead, lead away, take) captive(-s), drive (take) away.

From an unused root (probably identical with that of (H7617) shabah through the idea of subdivision into flashes or streamers (compare (H7632) shabiyb) meaning to flame; a gem (from its sparkle), probably the agate -- agate. see HEBREW (H7632) shabiyb

column7: captive (or returned) of God, two Israelites
column9: Or Shuwbanel {shoo-baw-ale'}; from (H7617) shabah (abbrev.) Or (H7725) shuwb and (H410) 'el; captive (or returned) of God; Shebuel or Shubael, the name of two Israelites -- Shebuel, Shubael. see HEBREW (H7617) shabah see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: a period of seven (days, years), heptad, week
column9: Or shabuan {shaw-boo'-ah}; also (feminine) shbu.ah {sheb-oo-aw'}; properly, passive participle of (H7650) shaba' as a denominative of (H7651) sheba'; literal, sevened, i.e. A week (specifically, of years) -- seven, week. see HEBREW (H7650) shaba' see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Feminine passive participle of (H7650) shaba'; properly, something sworn, i.e. An oath -- curse, oath, X sworn. see HEBREW (H7650) shaba'
Or shbiyth {sheb-eeth'}; from (H7617) shabah; exile, concretely, prisoners; figuratively, a former state of prosperity -- captive(-ity). see HEBREW (H7617) shabah

column8: commend, glory, keep in, praise, still, triumph
column9: A primitive root; properly, to address in a loud tone, i.e. (specifically) loud; figuratively, to pacify (as if by words) -- commend, glory, keep in, praise, still, triumph.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7623) shabach; to adulate, i.e. Adore -- praise. see HEBREW (H7623) shabach
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7626) shebet; a clan -- tribe. see HEBREW (H7626) shebet

column8: correction, dart, rod, scepter, staff, tribe
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to branch off; a scion, i.e. (literally) a stick (for punishing, writing, fighting, ruling, walking, etc.) Or (figuratively) a clan -- X correction, dart, rod, sceptre, staff, tribe.

column7: eleventh month in the Jewish calendar
column9: Of foreign origin; Shebat, a Jewish month -- Sebat.

column4: noun masculine; Adjective; noun masculine; noun feminine
column8: captivity, prisoners, take away, that was taken
column9: From (H7618) shbuw; exiled; captured; as noun, exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively); by extension, booty -- captive(-ity), prisoners, X take away, that was taken. see HEBREW (H7618) shbuw
From (H7617) shabah; captor; Shobi, an Ammonite -- Shobi. see HEBREW (H7617) shabah

column7: head of a family of gatekeepers
column9: For (H7629) Shobiy; Shobai, an Israelite -- Shobai. see HEBREW (H7629) Shobiy
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7632) shabiyb -- flame. see HEBREW (H7632) shabiyb
From the same as (H7616) shabab; flame (as split into tongues) -- spark. see HEBREW (H7616) shabab
Feminine of (H7628) shbiy; exile (abstractly or concretely and collectively) -- captives(-ity). see HEBREW (H7628) shbiy
Feminine of the same as (H7629) Shobiy; captivation; Shobjah, an Israelite -- Shachia (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7629) Shobiy
From the same as (H7640) shebel; a track or passage-way (as if flowing along) -- path. see HEBREW (H7640) shebel
From an unused root meaning to interweave; a netting for the hair -- caul.
Or shbi iy {sheb-ee-ee'}; ordinal from (H7657) shib'iym.; seventh -- seventh (time). see HEBREW (H7657) shib'iym.
From an unused root meaning to intwine; a netting (ornament to the capital of a column) -- net.

column8: checker, lattice, network, snare, wreathen work
column9: Feminine of (H7638) sabak; a net-work, i.e (in hunting) a snare, (in architecture) a ballustrade; also a reticulated ornament to a pillar -- checker, lattice, network, snare, wreath(-enwork). see HEBREW (H7638) sabak
From an unused root meaning to flow; a lady's train (as trailing after her) -- leg.

column8: branch, channel, ear of corn, water, flood, Shibboleth
column9: Or (feminine) shibboleth {shib-bo'-leth}; from the same as (H7640) shebel; a stream (as flowing); also an ear of grain (as growing out); by analogy, a branch -- branch, channel, ear (of corn), ((water-))flood, Shibboleth. Compare (H5451) cibboleth. see HEBREW (H7640) shebel see HEBREW (H5451) cibboleth
From the same as (H7640) shebel; a snail (as if floating in its own slime) -- snail. see HEBREW (H7640) shebel
Or (feminine) Sibmah {sib-maw'}; probably from (H1313) basam; spice; Sebam or Sibmah, a place in Moab -- Shebam, Shibmah, Sibmah. see HEBREW (H1313) basam
: or Shebnah {sheb-naw'}; from an unused root meaning to grow; growth; Shebna or Shebnah, an Israelite -- Shebna, Shebnah.

Or Shbanyahuw {sheb-an-yaw'-hoo}; from the same as (H7644) Shebna' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has grown (i.e. Prospered); Shebanjah, the name of three or four Israelites -- Shebaniah. see HEBREW (H7644) Shebna' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to be sated, satisfied or surfeited
column8: have enough, fill full, self, with, be to the full of, have plenty of, be satiated
column9: Or sabeay {saw-bay'-ah}; a primitive root; to sate, i.e. Fill to satisfaction (literally or figuratively) -- have enough, fill (full, self, with), be (to the) full (of), have plenty of, be satiate, satisfy (with), suffice, be weary of.
From (H7646) saba'; copiousness -- abundance, plenteous(- ness, -ly). see HEBREW (H7646) saba'
From (H7646) saba'; satisfaction (of food or (figuratively) joy) -- fill, full(-ness), satisfying, be satisfied. see HEBREW (H7646) saba'
From (H7646) saba'; satiated (in a pleasant or disagreeable sense) -- full (of), satisfied (with). see HEBREW (H7646) saba'

column8: adjure, charge by an oath, with an oath, feed to the full
column9: A primitive root; propr. To be complete, but used only as a denominative from (H7651) sheba'; to seven oneself, i.e. Swear (as if by repeating a declaration seven times) -- adjure, charge (by an oath, with an oath), feed to the full (by mistake for (H7646) saba'), take an oath, X straitly, (cause to, make to) swear. see HEBREW (H7651) sheba' see HEBREW (H7646) saba'

Or (masculine) shibrah {shib-aw'}; from (H7650) shaba'; a primitive cardinal number; seven (as the sacred full one); also (adverbially) seven times; by implication, a week; by extension, an indefinite number -- (+ by) seven(-fold),-s, (-teen, -teenth), -th, times). Compare (H7658) shib'anah. see HEBREW (H7650) shaba' see HEBREW (H7658) shib'anah

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column9: The same as (H7651) sheba'; seven; Sheba, the name of a place in Palestine, and of two Israelites -- Sheba. see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Feminine of (H7647) saba'; satiety -- fulness. see HEBREW (H7647) saba'
Feminine of (H7648) soba'; satiety -- (to have) enough, X till...be full, (un-)satiable, satisfy, X sufficiently. see HEBREW (H7648) soba'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7651) sheba' -- seven (times). see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Masculine of (H7651) sheba'; seven(-th); Shebah, a well in Palestine -- Shebah. see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Multiple of (H7651) sheba'; seventy -- seventy, threescore and ten (+ -teen). see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Prol. For the masculine of (H7651) sheba'; seven -- seven. see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'
Dual (adverbially) of (H7651) sheba'; seven- times -- seven(-fold, times). see HEBREW (H7651) sheba'

column7: probably to weave in checker (or plaited) work
column9: A primitive root; to interweave (colored) threads in squares; by implication (of reticulation) to inchase gems in gold -- embroider, set.
From (H7660) shabats; entanglement, i.e. (figuratively) perplexity -- anguish. see HEBREW (H7660) shabats
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of (H7733) Showbeq; to quit, i.e. Allow to remain -- leave, let alone. see HEBREW (H7733) Showbeq

Erroneously shabar (Nehemiah 2:13, Nehemiah 2:15) {shaw-bar'}; a primitive root; to scrutinize; by implication (of watching) to expect (with hope and patience) -- hope, tarry, view, wait. see HEBREW (H15) 'abeh
From (H7663) sabar; expectation -- hope. see HEBREW (H7663) sabar

column8: break down, off, in pieces, up, brokenhearted, bring to the birth, crush, destroy,
column9: A primitive root; to burst (literally or figuratively) -- break (down, off, in pieces, up), broken((-hearted)), bring to the birth, crush, destroy, hurt, quench, X quite, tear, view (by mistake for (H7663) sabar). see HEBREW (H7663) sabar
Denominative from (H7668) sheber; to deal in grain -- buy, sell. see HEBREW (H7668) sheber

column7: a breaking, fracture, crushing, breach, crash
column8: affliction, breach, breaking, broken-footed, bruise, crashing, destruction
column9: Or sheber {shay'-ber}; from (H7665) shabar; a fracture, figuratively, ruin; specifically, a solution (of a dream) -- affliction, breach, breaking, broken(-footed, -handed), bruise, crashing, destruction, hurt, interpretation, vexation. see HEBREW (H7665) shabar
The same as (H7667) sheber; grain (as if broken into kernels) -- corn, victuals. see HEBREW (H7667) sheber
The same as (H7667) sheber; Sheber, an Israelite -- Sheber. see HEBREW (H7667) sheber
From (H7665) shabar; rupture, i.e. A pang; figuratively, ruin -- breaking, destruction. see HEBREW (H7665) shabar
Plural of (H7667) sheber; ruins; Shebarim, a place in Palestine -- Shebarim. see HEBREW (H7667) sheber
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7660) shabats; to entangle, i.e. Perplex -- be astonished. see HEBREW (H7660) shabats

column8: cause to, let, make to cease, celebrate, cause make to fail
column9: A primitive root; to repose, i.e. Desist from exertion; used in many implied relations (causative, figurative or specific) -- (cause to, let, make to) cease, celebrate, cause (make) to fail, keep (sabbath), suffer to be lacking, leave, put away (down), (make to) rest, rid, still, take away.

column8: cease, sit still, loss of time
column9: From (H7673) shabath; rest, interruption, cessation -- cease, sit still, loss of time. see HEBREW (H7673) shabath

Infinitive of (H3427) yashab; properly, session; but used also concretely, an abode or locality -- place, seat. Compare (H3429) Yosheb bash-Shebeth. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H3429) Yosheb bash-Shebeth
Intensive from (H7673) shabath; intermission, i.e (specifically) the Sabbath -- (+ every) sabbath. see HEBREW (H7673) shabath
From (H7676) shabbath; a sabbatism or special holiday -- rest, sabbath. see HEBREW (H7676) shabbath
From (H7676) shabbath; restful; Shabbethai, the name of three Israelites -- Shabbethai. see HEBREW (H7676) shabbath
: a primitive root; to grow, i.e. (causatively) to enlarge, (figuratively) laud -- increase, magnify.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7679) saga'; to increase -- grow, be multiplied. see HEBREW (H7679) saga'

column7: father of one of David\'s heroes
column9: Probably from (H7686) shagah; erring; Shage, an Israelite -- Shage. see HEBREW (H7686) shagah

column8: defend, exalt, be excellent, be, set on high, lofty, be safe, set up on high,
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) lofty, especially inaccessible; by implication, safe, strong; used literally and figuratively --defend, exalt, be excellent, (be, set on) high, lofty, be safe, set up (on high), be too strong.

column7: to go astray, commit sin or error
column8: deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly
column9: A primitive root; to stray, i.e. (figuratively) sin (with more or less apology) -- X also for that, deceived, err, go astray, sin ignorantly.
From (H7683) shagag; a mistake or inadvertent transgression -- error, ignorance, at unawares; unwittingly. see HEBREW (H7683) shagag
A primitive root; to enlarge (especially upward, also figuratively) -- grow (up), increase.

column8: cause to go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, make to wander
column9: A primitive root; to stray (causatively, mislead), usually (figuratively) to mistake, especially (morally) to transgress; by extension (through the idea of intoxication) to reel, (figuratively) be enraptured -- (cause to) go astray, deceive, err, be ravished, sin through ignorance, (let, make to) wander.
From (H7682) sagab; aloft; Segub, the name of two Israelites -- Segub. see HEBREW (H7682) sagab
A primitive root; to peep, i.e. Glance sharply at -- look (narrowly).
From (H7679) saga'; (superlatively) mighty -- excellent, great. see HEBREW (H7679) saga'

column8: exceeding, greatly; many, much, sore, very
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7689) saggiy'; large (in size, quantity or number, also adverbial) -- exceeding, great(-ly); many, much, sore, very. see HEBREW (H7689) saggiy'
From (H7686) shagah; a moral mistake -- error. see HEBREW (H7686) shagah

column7: perhaps a wild passionate song with rapid changes of rhythm
column9: Or shiggayonah {shig-gaw-yo-naw'}; from (H7686) shagah; properly, aberration, i.e. (technically) a dithyramb or rambling poem -- Shiggaion, Shigionoth. see HEBREW (H7686) shagah
A primitive root; to copulate with -- lie with, ravish.
From (H7693) shagal; a queen (from cohabitation) -- queen. see HEBREW (H7693) shagal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7694) shegal; a (legitimate) queen -- wife. see HEBREW (H7694) shegal
A primitive root; to rave through insanity -- (be, play the) mad (man).
From (H7696) shaga'; craziness -- furiously, madness. see HEBREW (H7696) shaga'
From an unused root probably meaning to eject; the fetus (as finally expelled) -- that cometh of, increase.
Or shod {shode}; probably from (H7736) shuwd (in its original sense) contracted; the breast of a woman or animal (as bulging) -- breast, pap, teat. see HEBREW (H7736) shuwd
From (H7736) shuwd; a doemon (as malignant) -- devil. see HEBREW (H7736) shuwd

column8: desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoiled wasting
column9: Or showd (Job 5:21) {shode}; from (H7736) shuwd; violence, ravage -- desolation, destruction, oppression, robbery, spoil(-ed, -er, - ing), wasting. see HEBREW (H7736) shuwd
A primitive root; to abrade, i.e. Harrow a field -- break clods, harrow.

column7: to deal violently with, despoil, devastate, ruin
column8: dead, destroyer, oppress, robber, spoiler, utterly, lay waste
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be burly, i.e. (figuratively) powerful (passively, impregnable); by implication, to ravage -- dead, destroy(-er), oppress, robber, spoil(-er), X utterly, (lay) waste.

column8: country, field, ground, land, soil, wild
column9: Or saday {saw-dah'-ee}; from an unused root meaning to spread out; a field (as flat) -- country, field, ground, land, soil, X wild.
From (H7703) shadad; a wife (as mistress of the house) -- X all sorts, musical instrument. see HEBREW (H7703) shadad
From (H7703) shadad; the Almighty -- Almighty. see HEBREW (H7703) shadad
From the same as (H7704) sadeh and (H217) 'uwr; spreader of light; Shedejur, an Israelite -- Shedeur. see HEBREW (H7704) sadeh see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr

column7: a valley near the Dead Sea
column9: Plural from the same as (H7704) sadeh; flats; Siddim, a valley in Palestine -- Siddim. see HEBREW (H7704) sadeh
Apparently from (H7704) sadeh; a cultivated field; -- blasted, field. see HEBREW (H7704) sadeh
A primitive root; to scorch -- blast.
Or shiddaphown {shid-daw-fone'}; from (H7710) shadaph; blight -- blasted(-ing). see HEBREW (H7710) shadaph
(Aramaic) a primitive root; to endeavor -- labour.
From an unused root meaning to regulate; a row, i.e. Rank (of soldiers), story (of rooms) -- board, range.

column7: Bab. name of one of Daniel\'s companions
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Shadrak, the Bab. Name of one of Daniel's companions -- Shadrach.

column7: Bab. name of one of Daniel\'s companions
column9: (Aramaic) the same as (H7714) Shadrak -- Shadrach. see HEBREW (H7714) Shadrak

column7: one of a flock, a sheep (or goat)
column8: lesser, small cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep
column9: Or sey {say}; probably from (H7582) sha'ah through the idea of pushing out to graze; a member of a flock, i.e. A sheep or goat -- (lesser, small) cattle, ewe, goat, lamb, sheep. Compare (H2089) zeh. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah see HEBREW (H2089) zeh
From an unused root meaning to testify; a witness -- record.
From an unused root probably mean to blanch; a gem, probably the beryl (from its pale green color) -- onyx.
The same as (H7718) shoham; Shoham, an Israelite -- Shoham. see HEBREW (H7718) shoham

column8: ornament, round tire like the moon
column9: From the same as (H5469) cahar; a round pendant for the neck -- ornament, round tire like the moon. see HEBREW (H5469) cahar
From an unused root (akin to (H5375) nasa' and (H7722) show') meaning to rise; a rising -- arise. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa' see HEBREW (H7722) show'
Or (feminine) showtah {sho-aw'}; or shoah {sho-aw'}; from an unused root meaning to rush over; a tempest; by implication, devastation -- desolate(-ion), destroy, destruction, storm, wasteness.

Or shav {shav}; from the same as (H7722) show' in the sense of desolating; evil (as destructive), literally (ruin) or morally (especially guile); figuratively idolatry (as false, subjective), uselessness (as deceptive, objective; also adverbially, in vain) -- false(-ly), lie, lying, vain, vanity. see HEBREW (H7722) show'
From the same as (H7723) shav'; false; Sheva, an Israelite -- Sheva. see HEBREW (H7723) shav'

column8: break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down,
column9: A primitive root; to turn back (hence, away) transitively or intransitively, literally or figuratively (not necessarily with the idea of return to the starting point); generally to retreat; often adverbial, again -- ((break, build, circumcise, dig, do anything, do evil, feed, lay down, lie down, lodge, make, rejoice, send, take, weep)) X again, (cause to) answer (+ again), X in any case (wise), X at all, averse, bring (again, back, home again), call (to mind), carry again (back), cease, X certainly, come again (back), X consider, + continually, convert, deliver (again), + deny, draw back, fetch home again, X fro, get (oneself) (back) again, X give (again), go again (back, home), (go) out, hinder, let, (see) more, X needs, be past, X pay, pervert, pull in again, put (again, up again), recall, recompense, recover, refresh, relieve, render (again), requite, rescue, restore, retrieve, (cause to, make to) return, reverse, reward, + say nay, send back, set again, slide back, still, X surely, take back (off), (cause to, make to) turn (again, self again, away, back, back again, backward, from, off), withdraw.
From (H7725) shuwb; apostate, i.e. Idolatrous -- backsliding, frowardly, turn away (from margin). see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
The same as (H7726) showbab; rebellious; Shobab, the name of two Israelites -- Shobab. see HEBREW (H7726) showbab
From (H7725) shuwb; apostate, i.e. Heathenish or (actually) heathen -- backsliding. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From (H7725) shuwb; a return -- returning. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
For (H5441) cobek; a thicket, i.e. Interlaced branches -- thick boughs. see HEBREW (H5441) cobek
Perhaps for (H7730) sowbek; Shobak, a Syrian -- Shobach. see HEBREW (H7730) sowbek

column7: flowing, an Edomite, also two Israelites
column9: From the same as (H7640) shebel; overflowing; Shobal, the name of an Edomite and two Israelites -- Shobal. see HEBREW (H7640) shebel
Active participle from a primitive root meaning to leave (compare (H7662) shbaq); forsaking; Shobek, an Israelite -- Shobek. see HEBREW (H7662) shbaq
A primitive root; to retreat -- turn back.
A primitive root; to hedge in -- make to grow.
A primitive root; properly, to swell up, i.e. Figuratively (by implication of insolence) to devastate -- waste.

column7: to agree with, be like, resemble
column8: avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, be, make equal, lay,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to level, i.e. Equalize; figuratively, to resemble; by implication, to adjust (i.e. Counterbalance, be suitable, compose, place, yield, etc.) -- avail, behave, bring forth, compare, countervail, (be, make) equal, lay, be (make, a-)like, make plain, profit, reckon.
A primitive root; to destroy -- X substance (from the margin).
(Aramaic): corresponding to (H7737) shavah; to resemble -- make like. see HEBREW (H7737) shavah
From (H7737) shavah; plain; Shaveh, a place in Palestine -- Shaveh. see HEBREW (H7737) shavah

column7: a plain East of the Jordan
column9: From the same as (H7740) Shaveh and the dual of (H7151) qiryah; plain of a double city; Shaveh-Kirjathajim, a place East of the Jordan -- Shaveh Kiriathaim. see HEBREW (H7740) Shaveh see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah
A primitive root; to muse pensively -- meditate.
A primitive root; to sink, literally or figuratively -- bow down, incline, humble.

column7: a son of Abraham and Keturah
column9: From (H7743) shuwach; dell; Shuach, a son of Abraham -- Shuah. see HEBREW (H7743) shuwach
From (H7743) shuwach; a chasm -- ditch, pit. see HEBREW (H7743) shuwach
The same as (H7745) shuwchah; Shuchah, an Israelite -- Shuah. see HEBREW (H7745) shuwchah
Patronymic from (H7744) Shuwach; a Shuchite or descendant of Shuach -- Shuhite. see HEBREW (H7744) Shuwach
From (H7743) shuwach; humbly; Shucham, an Israelite -- Shuham. see HEBREW (H7743) shuwach
Patronymic from (H7748) Shuwcham; a Shuchamite (collectively) -- Shuhamites. see HEBREW (H7748) Shuwcham
Or (by permutation) cuwt {soot}; a primitive root; to detrude, i.e. (intransitively and figuratively) become derelict (wrongly practise; namely, idolatry) -- turn aside to.

column8: go about, through, to and fro, mariner, rower, run to and fro
column9: A primitive root; properly, to push forth; (but used only figuratively) to lash, i.e. (the sea with oars) to row; by implication, to travel -- go (about, through, to and fro), mariner, rower, run to and fro.
From (H7751) shuwt; a lash (literally or figuratively) -- scourge, whip. see HEBREW (H7751) shuwt

column7: to hedge or fence up or about
column9: A primitive root; to entwine, i.e. Shut in (for formation, protection or restraint) -- fence, (make an) hedge (up).
Or (feminine) sowkah {so-kaw'}; from (H7753) suwk; a branch (as interleaved) -- bough. see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
Or Sokoh {so-ko'}; or Sowkow {so-ko'}; from (H7753) suwk; Sokoh or Soko, the name of two places in Palestine -- Shocho, Shochoh, Sochoh, Soco, Socoh. see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
Probably patronymic from a name corresponding to (H7754) sowk (feminine); a Sukathite or descendant of an unknown Israelite named Sukah -- Suchathite.
From an unused root meaning to hang down; a skirt; by implication, a bottom edge -- hem, skirt, train.
Or sheylal (Micah 1:8) {shay-lawl'}; from (H7997) shalal; nude (especially bare-foot); by implication, captive -- spoiled, stripped. see HEBREW (H7997) shalal

column7: heroine of the Song of Solomon
column9: From (H7999) shalam; peaceful (with the article always prefixed, making it a pet name); the Shulammith, an epithet of Solomon's queen -- Shulamite. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column8: appoint, bring, call a name, care, cast in, change, charge,
column9: Or siym {seem}; a primitive root; to put (used in a great variety of applications, literal, figurative, inferentially, and elliptically) -- X any wise, appoint, bring, call (a name), care, cast in, change, charge, commit, consider, convey, determine, + disguise, dispose, do, get, give, heap up, hold, impute, lay (down, up), leave, look, make (out), mark, + name, X on, ordain, order, + paint, place, preserve, purpose, put (on), + regard, rehearse, reward, (cause to) set (on, up), shew, + stedfastly, take, X tell, + tread down, ((over-))turn, X wholly, work.

column8: command, give, lay, make, name, regard, set
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7760) suwm -- + command, give, lay, make, + name, + regard, set. see HEBREW (H7760) suwm
From an unused root meaning to exhale; garlic (from its rank odor) -- garlic.
Or Shomer {sho-mare'}; active participle of (H8104) shamar; keeper; Shomer, the name of two Israelites -- Shomer. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar
From an unused root meaning to rest; quiet; Shuni, an Israelite -- Shuni.
Patronymic from (H7764) Shuwniy; a Shunite (collectively) or descendants of Shuni -- Shunites. see HEBREW (H7764) Shuwniy
Probably from the same as (H7764) Shuwniy; quietly; Shunem, a place in Pal -- Shunem. see HEBREW (H7764) Shuwniy
Patrial from (H7766) Shuwnem; a Shunammitess, or female inhabitant of Shunem -- Shunamite. see HEBREW (H7766) Shuwnem
A primitive root; properly, to be free; but used only causatively and reflexively, to halloo (for help, i.e. Freedom from some trouble) -- cry (aloud, out), shout.
From (H7768) shava'; a halloo -- cry, riches. see HEBREW (H7768) shava'
The same as (H7769) shuwa'; Shua, a Canaanite -- Shua, Shuah. see HEBREW (H7769) shuwa'

column4: Adjective; proper name, of a people; noun masculine
column9: From (H7768) shava' in the original sense of freedom; a noble, i.e. Liberal, opulent; also (as noun in the derived sense) a halloo -- bountiful, crying, rich. see HEBREW (H7768) shava'

column7: probably nomads East of the Tigris and in the Syrian desert
column9: The same as (H7771) showa'; rich; Shoa, an Oriental people -- Shoa. see HEBREW (H7771) showa'
From (H7768) shava'; a halloo -- cry. see HEBREW (H7768) shava'
From (H7768) shava'; wealth; Shua, an Israelitess -- Shua. see HEBREW (H7768) shava'
Feminine of (H7773) sheva'; a hallooing -- crying. see HEBREW (H7773) sheva'
Or shunal {shoo-awl'}; from the same as (H8168) sho'al; a jackal (as a burrower) -- fox. see HEBREW (H8168) sho'al

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column9: The same as (H7776) shuw'al; Shual, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Shual. see HEBREW (H7776) shuw'al
Or shomer {sho-are'}: active participle of (H8176) sha'ar (as denominative from (H8179) sha'ar); a janitor -- doorkeeper, porter. see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar see HEBREW (H8179) sha'ar
A primitive root; properly, to gape, i.e. Snap at; figuratively, to overwhelm -- break, bruise, cover.
From (H8210) shaphak; poured; Shophak, a Syrian -- Shophach. see HEBREW (H8210) shaphak
Patronymic from (H8197) Shphuwpham; a Shuphamite (collectively) or descendants of Shephupham -- Shuphamite. see HEBREW (H8197) Shphuwpham
Or shophar {sho-far'}; from (H8231) shaphar in the original sense of incising; a cornet (as giving a clear sound) or curved horn -- cornet, trumpet. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
A primitive root; to run after or over, i.e. Overflow -- overflow, water.
From (H7783) shuwq; a street (as run over) -- street. see HEBREW (H7783) shuwq
From (H7783) shuwq; the (lower) leg (as a runner) -- hip, leg, shoulder, thigh. see HEBREW (H7783) shuwq
A primitive root; properly, to vanquish; by implication, to rule (causatively, crown) -- make princes, have power, reign. See (H5493) cuwr. see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr
A primitive root (identical with (H7786) suwr through the idea of reducing to pieces; compare (H4883) massowr); to saw -- cut. see HEBREW (H7786) suwr see HEBREW (H4883) massowr
A primitive root; properly, to turn, i.e. Travel about (as a harlot or a merchant) -- go, singular See also (H7891) shiyr. see HEBREW (H7891) shiyr

column8: behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H7788) shuwr through the idea of going round for inspection); to spy out, i.e. (generally) survey, (for evil) lurk for, (for good) care for -- behold, lay wait, look, observe, perceive, regard, see. see HEBREW (H7788) shuwr
From (H7889) Shiymown; a foe (as lying in wait) -- enemy. see HEBREW (H7889) Shiymown
From (H7788) shuwr; a wall (as going about) -- wall. see HEBREW (H7788) shuwr
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7791) shuwr -- wall. see HEBREW (H7791) shuwr

column7: a desert region Southwest of Pal. on E. border of Egypt
column9: The same as (H7791) shuwr; Shur, a region of the Desert -- Shur. see HEBREW (H7791) shuwr

column7: a head of cattle (bullock, ox, etc.)
column9: From (H7788) shuwr; a bullock (as a traveller) -- bull(-ock), cow, ox, wall (by mistake for (H7791) shuwr). see HEBREW (H7788) shuwr see HEBREW (H7791) shuwr
From (H7786) suwr in the primitive sense of (H5493) cuwr; properly, a ring, i.e. (by analogy) a row (adverbially) -- principal. see HEBREW (H7786) suwr see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr

column7: choice vines, a valley where Delilah lived
column9: The same as (H8321) soreq; a vine; Sorek, a valley in Palestine -- Sorek. see HEBREW (H8321) soreq

column8: be glad, greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice
column9: Or siys {sece}; a primitive root; to be bright, i.e. Cheerful -- be glad, X greatly, joy, make mirth, rejoice.
From (H7797) suws; joyful; Shavsha, an Israelite -- Shavsha. see HEBREW (H7797) suws

Or showshan {sho-shawn'}; or shoshan {sho- shawn'}; and (feminine) showshannah {sho-shan-naw'}; from (H7797) suws; a lily (from its whiteness), as a flower of arch. Ornament; also a (straight) trumpet (from the tubular shape): lily, Shoshannim. see HEBREW (H7797) suws
The same as (H7799) shuwshan; Shushan, a place in Persia -- Shushan. see HEBREW (H7799) shuwshan
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; a Shushankite (collectively) or inhabitants of some unknown place in Assyrian -- Susanchites.

Or (plural of former) Showshanniym aeduwth {sho-shan-neem' ay-dooth'}; from (H7799) shuwshan and (H5715) eduwth; lily (or trumpet) of assemblage; Shushan-Eduth or Shoshannim-Eduth, the title of a popular song -- Shoshannim-Eduth, Shushan-eduth. see HEBREW (H7799) shuwshan see HEBREW (H5715) eduwth
Probably from (H7582) sha'ah and the same as (H8520) Telach; crash of breakage; Shuthelach, the name of two Israelites -- Shuthelah. see HEBREW (H7582) sha'ah see HEBREW (H8520) Telach
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H5800) azab; to leave, i.e. (causatively) free -- deliver. see HEBREW (H5800) azab

column7: to catch sight of, look on
column9: A primitive root; to tan (by sun-burning); figuratively (as if by a piercing ray) to scan -- look up, see.
A primitive root; to twist (a thread of straw) -- twine.
From (H7817) shachach; sunk, i.e. Downcast -- + humble. see HEBREW (H7817) shachach
For (H7879) siyach; communion, i.e. (reflexively) meditation -- thought. see HEBREW (H7879) siyach
A primitive root; to donate, i.e. Bribe -- hire, give a reward.
From (H7809) shachad; a donation (venal or redemptive) -- bribe(-ry), gift, present, reward. see HEBREW (H7809) shachad
A primitive root; to swim; causatively, to inundate -- (make to) swim.

column8: bow self down, crouch, fall down flat, humbly beseech, do reverence, worship
column9: A primitive root; to depress, i.e. Prostrate (especially reflexive, in homage to royalty or God) -- bow (self) down, crouch, fall down (flat), humbly beseech, do (make) obeisance, do reverence, make to stoop, worship.
From (H7811) sachah; a pond (for swimming) -- to swim in. see HEBREW (H7811) sachah

column8: derision, laughter, to scorn, mocked, sport
column9: Or schoq {sekh-oke'}; from (H7832) sachaq; laughter (in merriment or defiance) -- derision, laughter(-ed to scorn, -ing), mocked, sport. see HEBREW (H7832) sachaq
From (H7835) shachar; dinginess, i.e. Perhaps soot -- coal. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From (H7812) shachah; pit -- pit. see HEBREW (H7812) shachah

column7: to bow, be bowed down, crouch
column8: bend, bow down, bring cast down, humble self, be bring low, stoop
column9: A primitive root; to sink or depress (reflexive or causative) -- bend, bow (down), bring (cast) down, couch, humble self, be (bring) low, stoop.
A primitive root; to tread out, i.e. Squeeze (grapes) -- press.

column8: kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter
column9: A primitive root; to slaughter (in sacrifice or massacre) -- kill, offer, shoot out, slay, slaughter.
A primitive root (identical with (H7819) shachat through the idea of striking); to hammer out -- beat. see HEBREW (H7819) shachat
From (H7819) shachat; slaughter -- killing. see HEBREW (H7819) shachat
From an unused root probably meaning to burn; inflammation, i.e. An ulcer; --boil, botch.

column7: that which springs of the same
column8: that which springs of the same
column9: Or cachiysh {saw-kheesh'}; from an unused root apparently meaning to sprout; after-growth -- (that) which springeth of the same.
From the same as (H7828) shachaph; a board (as chipped thin) -- cieled with. see HEBREW (H7828) shachaph
From (H7812) shachah; a pit-fall (literally or figuratively) -- destruction, pit. see HEBREW (H7812) shachah
From an unused root probably meaning to roar; a lion (from his characteristic roar) -- (fierce) lion.

column7: (an ingredient of the holy incense) perhaps onycha
column9: Apparently from the same as (H7826) shachal through some obscure idea, perhaps that of peeling off by concussion of sound; a scale or shell, i.e. The aromatic mussel. -- onycha. see HEBREW (H7826) shachal
From an unused root meaning to peel, i.e. Emaciate; the gull (as thin) -- cuckoo.
From the same as (H7828) shachaph; emaciation -- consumption. see HEBREW (H7828) shachaph
From an unused root apparently meaning to strut; haughtiness (as evinced by the attitude) -- X lion, pride.
From the same as (H7830) shachats; proudly; Shachatsom, a place in Palestine -- Shahazimah (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7830) shachats

column8: deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mocker, play, rejoice, laugh to scorn,
column9: A primitive root; to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play -- deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.

column7: to rub away, beat fine, pulverize
column9: A primitive root; to comminate (by trituration or attrition) -- beat, wear.
From (H7833) shachaq; a powder (as beaten small): by analogy, a thin vapor; by extension, the firmament -- cloud, small dust, heaven, sky. see HEBREW (H7833) shachaq
A primitive root (identical with (H7836) shachar through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn); to be dim or dark (in color) -- be black. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar

column7: to look early or diligently for
column8: do something betimes, enquire early, seek betimes, seek diligently early, in the morning
column9: A primitive root; properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking) -- (do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).

column8: dayspring, early, light, morning, whence rises
column9: From (H7836) shachar; dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial) -- day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar
Or shachowr {shaw-khore'}; from (H7835) shachar; properly, dusky, but also (absol.) Jetty -- black. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From (H7836) shachar; a dawning, i.e. (figuratively) juvenescence -- youth. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar
From (H7835) shachar; swarthy -- black. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From (H7836) shachar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has sought; Shecharjah, an Israelite -- Shehariah. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Dual of (H7837) shachar; double dawn; Shacharajim, an Israelite -- Shaharaim. see HEBREW (H7837) shachar

column8: batter, cast off, corrupter, thing, destroyer lose, mar, perish, spill,
column9: A primitive root; to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively) -- batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, X utterly, waste(-r).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7843) shachath -- corrupt, fault. see HEBREW (H7843) shachath
From (H7743) shuwach; a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction -- corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit. see HEBREW (H7743) shuwach

column7: swerver, perhaps revolter, deeds that swerve
column9: Or cet {sayt}; from (H7750) suwt; a departure from right, i.e. Sin -- revolter, that turn aside. see HEBREW (H7750) suwt
A primitive root; to deviate from duty -- decline, go aside, turn.

Feminine of a derivative (only in the plural shittiym {shit-teem'}; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as (H7850) shotet; the acacia (from its scourging thorns) -- shittah, shittim. See also (H1029) Beyth hash-Shittah. see HEBREW (H7850) shotet see HEBREW (H1029) Beyth hash-Shittah

column8: all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out
column9: A primitive root; to expand -- all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.
Active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from (H7752) showt) to flog; a goad -- scourge. see HEBREW (H7752) showt

column7: a place East of the Jordan, also a wadi perhaps West of Jer
column9: The same as the plural of (H7848) shittah; acacia trees; Shittim, a place East of the Jordan -- Shittim. see HEBREW (H7848) shittah

column7: to bear a grudge or cherish animosity against
column9: A primitive root; properly, to lurk for, i.e. Persecute -- hate, oppose self against.

column7: to be or act as adversary
column9: A primitive root; to attack, (figuratively) accuse -- (be an) adversary, resist.

column7: adversary, also the name of the superhuman adversary of God
column9: From (H7853) satan; an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good -- adversary, Satan, withstand. see HEBREW (H7853) satan
From (H7853) satan; opposition (by letter) -- accusation. see HEBREW (H7853) satan

column7: hostility, the name of a well near Gerar
column9: The same as (H7855) sitnah; Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal -- Sitnah. see HEBREW (H7855) sitnah

column7: to overflow, rinse or wash off
column8: drown, overflow whelm, rinse, run, rush, thoroughly wash away
column9: A primitive root; to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer -- drown, (over-)flow(- whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).
Or sheteph {shay'-tef}; from (H7857) shataph; a deluge (literally or figuratively) -- flood, outrageous, overflowing. see HEBREW (H7857) shataph
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a side -- side.
Active participle of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write; properly, a scribe, i.e. (by analogy or implication) an official superintendent or magistrate -- officer, overseer, ruler.
From the same as (H7860) shoter; magisterial; Shitrai, an Israelite -- Shitrai. see HEBREW (H7860) shoter
Probably from (H7737) shavah; a gift (as available) -- present. see HEBREW (H7737) shavah
From the same as (H7721) sow' by permutation; elevation -- excellency. see HEBREW (H7721) sow'
For (H7724) Shva'; Sheja, an Israelite -- Sheva (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7724) Shva'
From (H7863) siy'; peak; Sion, the summit of Mt. Hermon -- Sion. see HEBREW (H7863) siy'
From the same as (H7722) show'; ruin; Shijon, a place in Palestine --Shihon. see HEBREW (H7722) show'
A primitive root; properly, to become aged, i.e. (by implication) to grow gray -- (be) grayheaded.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7867) siyb -- elder. see HEBREW (H7867) siyb
From (H7867) siyb; old age -- age. see HEBREW (H7867) siyb
By permutation from (H7725) shuwb; a return (of property) -- captivity. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From (H3427) yashab; residence -- while...lay. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab

column8: be gray grey hoar, old age
column9: Feminine of (H7869) seyb; old age -- (be) gray (grey hoar,-y) hairs (head,-ed), old age. see HEBREW (H7869) seyb
From (H7734) suwg; a withdrawal (into a private place) -- pursuing. see HEBREW (H7734) suwg
A primitive root probably meaning to boil up (compare (H7736) shuwd); used only as denominative from (H7875) siyd; to plaster -- plaister. see HEBREW (H7736) shuwd see HEBREW (H7875) siyd
From (H7874) siyd; lime (as boiling when slacked) -- lime, plaister. see HEBREW (H7874) siyd
A primitive root; to keep in memory -- be unmindful. (Render Deuteronomy 32:18, \"A Rock bore thee, thou must recollect; and (yet) thou hast forgotten,\" etc.)
Of unknown derivation; Shiza, an Is. -- Shiza.

column8: commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk with
column9: A primitive root; to ponder, i.e. (by implication) converse (with oneself, and hence, aloud) or (transitively) utter -- commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk (with).

column8: babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk
column9: From (H7878) siyach; a contemplation; by implication, an utterance -- babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk. see HEBREW (H7878) siyach
From (H7878) siyach; a shoot (as if uttered or put forth), i.e. (generally) shrubbery -- bush, plant, shrub. see HEBREW (H7878) siyach
Feminine of (H7879) siyach; reflection; be extension, devotion -- meditation, prayer. see HEBREW (H7879) siyach
For (H7745) shuwchah; a pit-fall -- pit. see HEBREW (H7745) shuwchah

column7: a stream on the border of Egypt
column9: Or Shichowr {shee-khore'}; or Shichor {shee-khore'}; probably from (H7835) shachar; dark, i.e. Turbid; Shichor, a stream of Egypt -- Shihor, Sihor. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From the same as (H7883) Shiychowr and (H3835) laban; darkish whiteness; Shichor-Libnath, a stream of Palestine -- Shihor-libnath. see HEBREW (H7883) Shiychowr see HEBREW (H3835) laban
From (H7751) shuwt; an oar; also (compare (H7752) showt) a scourge (figuratively) -- oar, scourge. see HEBREW (H7751) shuwt see HEBREW (H7752) showt

column7: perhaps "he whose it is", a Messianic title
column9: From (H7951) shalah; tranquil; Shiloh, an epithet of the Messiah -- Shiloh. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
Or Shiloh {shee-lo'}; or Shiylow {shee-lo'}; or Shilow {shee-lo'}; from the same as (H7886) Shiyloh; Shiloh, a place in Palestine -- Shiloh. see HEBREW (H7886) Shiyloh
Or Shiyloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; or Shiloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; from (H7887) Shiyloh; a Shilonite or inhabitant of Shiloh -- Shilonite. see HEBREW (H7887) Shiyloh
Apparently for (H3452) yshiymown; desert; Shimon, an Israelite -- Shimon. see HEBREW (H3452) yshiymown
From an unused root meaning to urinate; urine -- piss.

Or (the original form) shuwr (1 Sam. 18:6) {shoor}; a primitive root (identical with (H7788) shuwr through the idea of strolling minstrelsy); to sing -- behold (by mistake for (H7789) shuwr), sing(-er, -ing man, - ing woman). see HEBREW (H7788) shuwr see HEBREW (H7789) shuwr
Or feminine shiyrah {shee-raw'}; from (H7891) shiyr; a song; abstractly, singing -- musical(-ick), X sing(-er, -ing), song. see HEBREW (H7891) shiyr
From an unused root meaning to bleach, i.e. Whiten; white, i.e. Marble. See (H8336) shesh. see HEBREW (H8336) shesh
From the same as (H7893) shayish; whiteness; Shisha, an Israelite -- Shisha. see HEBREW (H7893) shayish
Or Shuwshaq {shoo-shak'}; of Egyptian derivation; Shishak, an Egyptian king -- Shishak.

column8: apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay up, let alone, look,
column9: A primitive root; to place (in a very wide application) -- apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay (up), let alone, X look, make, mark, put (on), + regard, set, shew, be stayed, X take.
From (H7896) shiyth; a dress (as put on) -- attire. see HEBREW (H7896) shiyth
From (H7896) shiyth; scrub or trash, i.e. Wild growth of weeds or briers (as if put on the field) -- thorns. see HEBREW (H7896) shiyth
From (H5526) cakak in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a brier (as of a hedge) -- prick. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
From (H5526) cakak in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a booth (as interlaced) -- tabernacle. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak see HEBREW (H7753) suwk

column8: cast down, lay self down, make to lie down, down to sleep, still with, lodge, ravish,
column9: A primitive root; to lie down (for rest, sexual connection, decease or any other purpose) -- X at all, cast down, ((lover-))lay (self) (down), (make to) lie (down, down to sleep, still with), lodge, ravish, take rest, sleep, stay.
From (H7901) shakab; a lying down (of dew, or for the sexual act) -- X carnally, copulation, X lay, seed. see HEBREW (H7901) shakab
From (H7901) shakab; a (sexual) lying with -- X lie. see HEBREW (H7901) shakab
A primitive root; to roam (through lust) -- in the morning (by mistake for (H7925) shakam). see HEBREW (H7925) shakam
Feminine of (H7900) sok in the sense of (H7899) sek; a dart (as pointed like a thorn) -- barbed iron. see HEBREW (H7900) sok see HEBREW (H7899) sek
From an unused root apparently meaning to surmount; an observatory (with the article); Seku, a place in Palestine -- Sechu.
From the same as (H7906) Sekuw; observant, i.e. (concretely) the mind -- heart. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw
Infinitive of (H7921) shakol; bereavement -- loss of children, spoiling. see HEBREW (H7921) shakol

column8: barren, bereaved robbed of children whelps
column9: Or shakkul {shak-kool'}; from (H7921) shakol; bereaved -- barren, bereaved (robbed) of children (whelps). see HEBREW (H7921) shakol
Or shikkor {shik-kore'}; from (H7937) shakar; intoxicated, as a state or a habit -- drunk(-ard, -en, -en man). see HEBREW (H7937) shakar
Or shakeach {shaw-kay'-akh}; a primitive root; to mislay, i.e. To be oblivious of, from want of memory or attention -- X at all, (cause to) forget.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7911) shakach through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing; to discover (literally or figuratively) -- find. see HEBREW (H7911) shakach
From (H7911) shakach; oblivious -- forget. see HEBREW (H7911) shakach
Feminine from the same as (H7906) Sekuw; a conspicuous object -- picture. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw
Intensive perhaps from the same as (H7906) Sekuw in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a knife (as pointed or edged) -- knife. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
From (H7936) sakar; a man at wages by the day or year -- hired (man, servant), hireling. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
Feminine of (H7916) sakiyr; a hiring -- that is hired. see HEBREW (H7916) sakiyr

column8: appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set
column9: A primitive root; to weave (i.e. Lay) a trap; figuratively, (through the idea of secreting) to allay (passions; physically, abate a flood) -- appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set.

column8: consider, expert, instruct, prosper, deal prudently, give skillful, have good success, teach,
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make or act) circumspect and hence, intelligent -- consider, expert, instruct, prosper, (deal) prudent(-ly), (give) skill(-ful), have good success, teach, (have, make to) understand(-ing), wisdom, (be, behave self, consider, make) wise(- ly), guide wittingly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7919) sakal -- consider. see HEBREW (H7919) sakal

column8: bereave of children, barren, cast calf fruit, make childless, deprive, destroy
column9: A primitive root; properly, to miscarry, i.e. Suffer abortion; by analogy, to bereave (literally or figuratively) -- bereave (of children), barren, cast calf (fruit, young), be (make) childless, deprive, destroy, X expect, lose children, miscarry, rob of children, spoil.

column8: discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise
column9: Or sekel {say'-kel}; from (H7919) sakal; intelligence; by implication, success -- discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise. see HEBREW (H7919) sakal

column8: to have after loss of others
column9: Plural from (H7921) shakol; childlessness (by continued bereavements) -- to have after loss of others. see HEBREW (H7921) shakol
(Aramaic) from (H7920) skal; intelligence -- understanding. see HEBREW (H7920) skal

column8: arise, be up, get oneself up, rise up early betimes, morning
column9: A primitive root; properly, to incline (the shoulder to a burden); but used only as denominative from (H7926) shkem; literally, to load up (on the back of man or beast), i.e. To start early in the morning -- (arise, be up, get (oneself) up, rise up) early (betimes), morning. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
From (H7925) shakam; the neck (between the shoulders) as the place of burdens; figuratively, the spur of a hill -- back, X consent, portion, shoulder. see HEBREW (H7925) shakam

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: ridge, a district in Northern Palestine, also a son of Hamor
column9: The same as (H7926) shkem; ridge; Shekem, a place in Palestine -- Shechem. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
For (H7926) shkem; Shekem, the name of a Hivite and two Israelites -- Shechem. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
Feminine of (H7926) shkem; the shoulder-bone -- shoulder blade. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
Patronymic from (H7928) Shekem; a Shikmite (collectively), or descendants of Shekem -- Shichemites. see HEBREW (H7928) Shekem

column8: abide, continue, cause to, make to dweller, have habitation, inhabit, lay, place,
column9: A primitive root (apparently akin (by transmission) to (H7901) shakab through the idea of lodging; compare (H5531) cikluwth, (H7925) shakam); to reside or permanently stay (literally or figuratively) -- abide, continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-er), have habitation, inhabit, lay, place, (cause to) remain, rest, set (up). see HEBREW (H5531) cikluwth see HEBREW (H7925) shakam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7931) shakan -- cause to dwell, have habitation. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan
From (H7931) shakan; a residence -- habitation. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan
From (H7931) shakan; a resident; by extension, a fellow-citizen -- inhabitant, neighbour, nigh. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan

column7: Yah has taken up His abode, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or (prol.) Shkanyahuw {shek-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H7931) shakan and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has dwelt; Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites -- Shecaniah, Shechaniah. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: earn wages, hire out self, reward, surely
column9: Or (by permutation) cakar (Ezra 4:5) {saw-kar'}; a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to (H3739) karah through the idea of temporary purchase; compare (H7937) shakar); to hire -- earn wages, hire (out self), reward, X surely. see HEBREW (H3739) karah see HEBREW (H7937) shakar

column7: to be or become drunk or drunken
column8: be filled with drink abundantly, be, make drunken, be merry
column9: A primitive root; to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence -- (be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of (H8248) shaqah.) see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah
From (H7936) sakar; wages -- reward, sluices. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
From (H7936) sakar; payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit -- hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
The same as (H7939) sakar; recompense; Sakar, the name of two Israelites -- Sacar. see HEBREW (H7939) sakar
From (H7937) shakar; an intoxicant, i.e. Intensely alcoholic liquor -- strong drink, + drunkard, strong wine. see HEBREW (H7937) shakar

column7: a city on N.W. border of Judah
column9: For (H7943) shikkarown; drunkenness, Shikkeron, a place in Palestine -- Shicron. see HEBREW (H7943) shikkarown
From (H7937) shakar; intoxication -- (be) drunken(-ness). see HEBREW (H7937) shakar
From (H7952) shalah abbrev.; a fault -- error. see HEBREW (H7952) shalah
For the rel. (H834) 'aher; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix; on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever -- cause, sake. see HEBREW (H834) 'aher
For (H7600) sha'anan; tranquil -- being at ease. see HEBREW (H7600) sha'anan
A primitive root; to space off; intensive (evenly) to make equidistant -- equally distant, set in order.
From (H7947) shalab; a spacer or raised interval, i.e. The stile in a frame or panel -- ledge. see HEBREW (H7947) shalab
A primitive root; properly, meaning to be white; used only as denominative from (H7950) sheleg; to be snow-white (with the linen clothing of the slain) -- be as snow. see HEBREW (H7950) sheleg
From (H7949) shalag; snow (probably from its whiteness) -- snow(-y). see HEBREW (H7949) shalag

column7: to be quiet or at ease
column8: be happy, prosper, be in safety
column9: Or shalav (Job 3:26) {shaw-lav'}; a primitive root; to be tranquil, i.e. Secure or successful -- be happy, prosper, be in safety.
A primitive root (probably identical with (H7953) shalah through the idea of educing); to mislead -- deceive, be negligent. see HEBREW (H7953) shalah

A primitive root (rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of (H5394) nashal, (H7997) shalal and their congeners through the idea of extracting); to draw out or off, i.e. Remove (the soul by death) -- take away. see HEBREW (H5394) nashal see HEBREW (H7997) shalal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7951) shalah; to be secure -- at rest. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H7952) shalah; a wrong -- thing amiss. see HEBREW (H7952) shalah
The same as (H7596) sh'elah (shortened); request; Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite -- Shelah. see HEBREW (H7596) sh'elah
From the same as (H3851) lahab with sibilant prefix; a flare of fire -- (flaming) flame. see HEBREW (H3851) lahab
Or slayv {sel-awv'}; by orthographical variation from (H7951) shalah through the idea of sluggishness; the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight) -- quails.
From (H7951) shalah; security -- prosperity. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) or shaluwth (Aramaic) {shaw-looth'}; from the same as (H7955) shalah; a fault -- error, X fail, thing amiss. see HEBREW (H7955) shalah

column8: being at ease, peaceable, in prosperity, quietness, wealthy
column9: Or shaleyv {shaw-lave'}; feminine shlevah {shel-ay-vaw'}; from (H7951) shalah; tranquil; (in a bad sense) careless; abstractly, security -- (being) at ease, peaceable, (in) prosper(-ity), quiet(-ness), wealthy. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
From (H7951) shalah; security (genuine or false) -- abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7962) shalvah; safety -- tranquillity. See also (H7961) shalev. see HEBREW (H7962) shalvah see HEBREW (H7961) shalev

Or shilluach {shil-loo'-akh}; from (H7971) shalach; (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower -- presents, have sent back. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: well,  favor, friend, great, good health, perfect,
column9: Or shalom {shaw-lome'}; from (H7999) shalam; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. Health, prosperity, peace -- X do, familiar, X fare, favour, + friend, X great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, X wholly. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
Or shillum {shil-loom'}; from (H7999) shalam; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee -- recompense, reward. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or (shorter) Shallum {shal-loom'}; the same as (H7966) shilluwm; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites -- Shallum. see HEBREW (H7966) shilluwm

column7: one of the postexilic wall builders
column9: Probably for (H7967) Shalluwm; Shallun, an Israelite -- Shallum. see HEBREW (H7967) Shalluwm

column8: fork, oftentimes, third, thirteen three, thrice
column9: Or shalosh {shaw-loshe'}; masculine shlowshah {shel-o-shaw'}; or shloshah {shel-o-shaw'}; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) Thrice -- + fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare (H7991) shaliysh. see HEBREW (H7991) shaliysh
Or shloshiym {shel-o-sheem'}; multiple of (H7969) shalowsh; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth -- thirty, thirtieth. Compare (H7991) shaliysh. see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh see HEBREW (H7991) shaliysh

A primitive root; to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications) -- X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, X earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7971) shalach -- put, send. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: dart, plant, put off, sword, weapon
column9: From (H7971) shalach; a missile of attack, i.e. Spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. Branch -- dart, plant, X put off, sword, weapon. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach
The same as (H7973) shelach; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch -- Salah, Shelah. Compare (H7975) Shiloach. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach see HEBREW (H7975) Shiloach

Or (in imitation of (H7974) Shelach) Shelach (Neh. 3:15) {sheh'-lakh}; from (H7971) shalach; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of Jerusalem -- Shiloah, Siloah. see HEBREW (H7974) Shelach see HEBREW (H7971) shalach
Feminine of (H7964) shilluwach; a shoot -- branch. see HEBREW (H7964) shilluwach
From (H7973) shelach; missive, i.e. Armed; Shilchi, an Israelite -- Shilhi. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach
Plural of (H7973) shelach; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine -- Shilhim. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach
From (H7971) shalach; a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal -- table. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: bear, have rule, have dominion, give have power
column9: A primitive root; to dominate, i.e. Govern; by implication, to permit -- (bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.

column8: have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be make ruler
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7980) shalat -- have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
From (H7980) shalat; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. Protecting the person) -- shield. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) from (H7980) shalat; a potentate; --power. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) or shilton {shil-tone'}; corresponding to (H7983) shiltown -- ruler. see HEBREW (H7983) shiltown
(Aramaic) from (H7981) shlet; empire (abstractly or concretely) -- dominion. see HEBREW (H7981) shlet
Feminine from (H7980) shalat; a vixen -- imperious. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
From (H7951) shalah; privacy -- + quietly. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
Feminine from (H7953) shalah; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth) -- young one. see HEBREW (H7953) shalah

column8: governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler
column9: From (H7980) shalat; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior -- governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7989) shalliyt; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier -- captain, be lawful, rule(- r). see HEBREW (H7989) shalliyt

column8: captain, instrument of music, great lord, great measure, prince, three
column9: Or shalowsh (1 Chron. 11:11; 12:18) {shaw- loshe'}; or shalosh (2 Sam. 23:13) {shaw-loshe'}; from (H7969) shalowsh; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute); also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah); also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. The highest) -- captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh

column8: third part, rank, time, three years old
column9: Ordinal from (H7969) shalowsh; third; feminine a third (part); by extension, a third (day, year or time); specifically, a third-story cell) -- third (part, rank, time), three (years old). see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh

column8: adventure, cast away, down, forth, off, out, hurl, pluck,
column9: A primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively) -- adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.
From (H7993) shalak; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea) -- cormorant. see HEBREW (H7993) shalak
From (H7993) shalak; a felling (of trees) -- when cast. see HEBREW (H7993) shalak

column7: (gate of) casting forth, a temple gate on the west side
column9: The same as (H7995) shalleketh; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem -- Shalleketh. see HEBREW (H7995) shalleketh

column8: let fall, make self a prey, of purpose, make a, take spoil
column9: A primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder -- let fall, make self a prey, X of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.
From (H7997) shalal; booty -- prey, spoil. see HEBREW (H7997) shalal

column8: make amends, make an end, finish, full, give again, make good, repay again
column9: A primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate); figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications) -- make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7999) shalam; to complete, to restore -- deliver, finish. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7965) shalowm; prosperity -- peace. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm

column7: a sacrifice for alliance or friendship, peace offering
column9: From (H7999) shalam; properly, requital, i.e. A (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks -- peace offering. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
